Name: Xel'Naga Void Array
Description: Can load and unload units between all Xel'Naga Void Arrays on the field. Can transform into a mobile Flight Mode.

Root.Tooltip: Orders selected units to move to the target area or follow the target unit. Moving units will not engage enemies.
Root.Name: Move

Root.Tooltip: Orders selected units to cancel all orders and stop moving.
Root.Name: Stop

Root.Tooltip: Orders selected units to stay where they are and attack enemies that are within range. Units will neither chase down enemies nor move to engage.
Root.Name: Hold Position

Root.Tooltip: Orders selected units to patrol between their current position and the target area. Units will attack enemies and move to engage nearby enemies.
Root.Name: Patrol

Root.Tooltip: Orders selected units to move to the target point, fighting nearby enemies along the way. Targeting a unit with the Attack command orders that it be attacked until it is destroyed.
Root.Name: Attack

Root.Tooltip: Orders selected units to move to the target area or follow the target unit. Scan-moving units will not engage enemies.
Root.Name: Scan Move

Root.Tooltip: Reverts the Xel'Naga Void Array back to Flight Mode, allowing it to move.
Root.Name: Flight Mode

Root.Tooltip: Loads units into the Xel'Naga Void Array's Matrix.
Root.Name: Load

Root.Tooltip: Units loaded into the Xel'Naga Void Array network will no longer automatically exit at this location.
Root.Name: Auto-Unload Off

Root.Tooltip: Grants the Xel'Naga Void Array unlimited capacity.
Root.Name: Infinite Void

Root.Tooltip: Unloads all units at the current location.
Root.Name: Unload

Root.Tooltip: Units loaded into a Xel'Naga Void Array may be unloaded at any other Xel'Naga Void Array.
Root.Name: Transfer Link

Root.Tooltip: Selects the Void Array currently in Auto-Unload mode.
Root.Name: Select Wormhole Exit

Root.Tooltip: Designates this Xel'Naga Void Array as the primary exit point. Units loaded in any Xel'Naga Void Array will automatically unload at this location.
Root.Name: Auto-Unload On

Root.Tooltip: This upgrade unlocks at Commander Level 13.
Root.Name: Shield Boosters

Root.Tooltip: Nearby units regenerate an additional 2 shields per second.
Root.Name: Shield Boosters
